ine in the classical era up to the eve of British colonialism. In addition to its cultural and historical contributions to South Asian Studies, the medical narratives discussed in the book contribute fresh perspectives on medicine and ethics in general and, in particular, notions of health and illness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aMedical literaturezIndiaxHistory and criticism. 0aMedicine, AyurvedicxHistory. 0aSanskrit literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : India and South Asian Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Hindu Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438443881423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438443881/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles